    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who makes SiteTuff products?",
            "answer": "<p>SiteTuff is a brand from <strong>Premier Diamond Products (PDP)</strong>, established in 1990. Every SiteTuff diamond blade, core drill and SDS bit is developed, tested and produced using PDP's 25+ years of diamond tooling expertise. The range is designed specifically for common UK construction materials.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I use SiteTuff dry cores without water?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. SiteTuff dry diamond cores are specifically designed for <strong>dry drilling</strong> \u2014 no water supply is required. The counter-clockwise spiral on the core body assists debris dispersal while drilling, reducing the risk of jamming. They are designed for use on facing bricks, concrete blocks and York stone.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What materials can SiteTuff diamond blades cut?",
            "answer": "<p>SiteTuff diamond blades cover a wide range of materials including <strong>concrete, building blocks, bricks, asphalt, tiles, cement board</strong> and general construction materials. Different blade specifications are available for different materials \u2014 the STC range is optimised for concrete and building materials, while specialist blades are available for tiles and mortar raking.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What sizes of SiteTuff diamond blades are available?",
            "answer": "<p>SiteTuff diamond blades are available in the most common professional sizes: <strong>115mm (4.5\"), 230mm (9\") and 300mm (12\")</strong>. These fit standard angle grinders, petrol saws and bench saws used on UK construction sites. The 230mm size is the most popular for general site cutting.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is included in the SiteTuff 12-piece dry core set?",
            "answer": "<p>The SiteTuff ST-DC-12 set includes <strong>5 dry diamond cores</strong> (42mm, 52mm, 65mm, 117mm and 127mm), a <strong>chuck adaptor</strong>, <strong>SDS adaptor</strong>, <strong>1/2\" to 1/2\" extension</strong>, <strong>drift key</strong> and a <strong>taper pilot drill</strong> \u2014 all in a professional carry case. Everything you need for core drilling through common UK construction materials.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on SiteTuff products?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full SiteTuff range including diamond blades, dry cores and SDS drill bits. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
